  "text": "Six frames are generated in one generation. This comes from a consideration of the established limitations of human memory, which enable the comparison of a maximum of nine objects at one time [CITATION_1] . We thus considered six to be the suitable number of design samples provided for evaluation in a single generation. The customer evaluates each frame according to a five-grade scale based on his/her degree of satisfaction. The evaluation score is regarded as a fitness value in the GA.",
